myorder
Class MyOrder

java.lang.Object
  myorder.MyOrder

public class MyOrder
extends java.lang.Object

This is a singleton class which holds all configuration settings which required to integrate the payment SDK with the app.

register

public void register()
              throws java.lang.Exception
Starts the registration of a new mobile phone number. The process needs to be verified with a SMS code before the account is activated with verifyRegistration. Note that the mobilePhone is set as a property in MyOrder instance.

Throws:
java.lang.Exception - If registration fails
See Also:
verifyRegistration(String, String)

verifyRegistration

public void verifyRegistration(java.lang.String activationCode,
                               java.lang.String newPassword)
                        throws java.lang.Exception
Verifies a registered phone number started on register with the received SMS code and sets a new password. If the verification succeds then a login is automatically performed. Note that the mobilePhone is set as a property in MyOrder instance.

Parameters:
activationCode - SMS code received when registering
newPassword - New password to be set
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - If verification fails
See Also:
register()
